However, it is estimated that about 10% of cancers are caused by heredity.
Many remain completely unexplained.
For the Canadian Cancer Society, the fight against tobacco addiction remains a priority, despite the decline in the number of smokers.
Smoking is responsible for 85% of cases of lung cancer.
It is also a risk factor for several other cancers.
It severely damages people’s health.
“Today, there are 1.5 million smokers in Quebec,” said Beaulieu.
Encouraging data: 10 years after quitting smoking, the risk of dying of cancer is reduced by half.
The weight
According to the Canadian Cancer Society, overweight and obesity also promote the onset of the disease.
They appear to increase the risk of breast, intestinal, gastrointestinal, esophageal, pancreatic and uterine cancers.
“Research shows that regular physical activity throughout life protects against colorectal cancer,” he adds.
The Diet
The organization also recommends limiting the consumption of red meat.
