<0xC5><0xA0>imon Ornest: At our concerts we want to collect positive energy
What do you think will happen in less than a month from the end of the world?
This is one of those disaster reports that we people like to jump to.
With our band The Tap Tap, we are more amused about it and say that we are the only band in the world that can collect enough positive energy to stop or prevent the world from falling.
In December, you will also realize a unique project with three concerts against the end of the world.
Can you introduce the project to our readers?
This is a nationwide charity event that we have been planning for two years.
For this, we want to use the marketing potential of the Maya calendar, whose end is predicted for December 21st at 11:10 am.
On the day before, i.e. on December 20, three concerts will take place simultaneously in Prague, Brno and Ostrava from 21:00.
The end of the concerts is said to be around the time when the Mayan calendar ends on the Pacific island of Kiribati, which is in a time zone about 12 hours ahead of us.
From whom does this idea come?
Initially probably from me, then we designed the idea together with our graphic designer Honza Augusta.
In doing so, we not only want to collect enough positive energy to prevent the collapse of the world, but we also want to reflect together with the public on the state in which we once pass on this world to our children.
On the occasion of the end of the Mayan calendar, we have also developed a unique collection of shoes, t-shirts, bags and keychains against the end of the world, with the purchase of which via www.e-tap.cz people can also support us.
The band The Tap Tap, together with other performers, has also recorded the so-called hymn against the decline of the world with the title "The decline of the world falls out".
The anthem is already very popular on YouTube today. Will it also be performed at the benefit concerts?
Of course, and finally, assuming that everything works and the world does not fall...
The anthem is to be sung by all the performers at all three concerts at the same time.
In addition, the hymns are broadcast live together in a live broadcast by Czech TV.
The text of the hymn comes from Tom<0xC3><0xA1><0xC5><0xA1> Han<0xC3><0xA1>k, who also plays the main character of Jesus in the video clip, also Xindl X sings with...
