The police authorities no longer prosecute adults over the age of 21 for possession to a small extent. This will be allowed by law as soon as the new laws come into force in the next few weeks.
But prosecutors in the more conservative districts of Colorado have announced they are continuing to prosecute existing marijuana offenses and are still citing people in court.
At the same time, several cities, from suburban Denver to the Western Mountains, are agreeing to block new, state-licensed marijuana businesses from opening in their communities.
