And he’s not the only professor who offers courses on the “end of the world” this semester, which should be the last in history.
In Temple, Assistant Professor Barry Vacker gives the course "Media, Culture and the End of the World."
Every week, students study apocalyptic topics such as nuclear war, zombies, viruses and germs, and global warming.
“We analyze why these ideas spread over time,” he said, as well as the way hypothetical scenarios are offered that lead to a certain human behavior.
If nuclear material gets into the hands of terrorists, for example, a war could break out.
